  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\n>As a user,\r\n>I want easily see what requires my attention in the Activity Center,\r\n>So that I can promptly act on the most important notifications to me.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nNowadays, the new Activity Center is using the old Notification Center behavior for marking notifications as read. We should implement the new rules:\r\n\r\n1. With CTA (call to action) - should stay *unread* until the user acts on it.\r\n2. Without CTA - should loose *unread indicator* and go down the list after the user opens the AC or the same tab again.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior about ordering\r\n\r\nNotifications should be ordered by timestamp descending and ID descending. This is the current behavior in status-go. Unread notifications should not be grouped at the top because the user can use the read/unread toggle button to easily find which notifications require their attention.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior for non-CTA notifications\r\n\r\nNon-CTA notifications should be automatically marked as read if they’re visible on screen, according to the current active tab (which dictates which types of notifications are displayed). If the user is in the special All tab then notifications of any type should be taken in consideration. For example, if the user opens the Activity Center, unread notifications are displayed with blue dots, but once the user switches to a different tab or go to another screen, when they open the Activity Center in the same tab, non-CTA notifications that were unread won’t have the unread blue dot anymore and they’ll be marked as read in the local database.\r\n",
