    "body": "Update (2023-01-19): After a new round of reviews about how should notifications be marked as read/unread, designers, PO and devs from mobile/desktop aligned the following:\r\n\r\n- Designers will soon update Figma with the most up-to-date specs so that developers can start the implementation work.\r\n- Developers will try to keep written specs about all things related to the AC, in order to complement the Figma specs.\r\n- All notifications will be marked as read by some user action, i.e. the concept of non-CTA notifications will become meaningless. For example, if the user was mentioned in a group chat, the user should see a unread notification in the AC, and pressing on it should open the chat and scroll to the mention. When the mention is visible on screen, then the notification will be marked as read.\r\n- Notifications should always be displayed chronologically. This is the current status-go behavior, so nothing to do here.\r\n- In both mobile and desktop apps, users should be able to do mass operations to mark notifications as read. This is missing in the new mobile design, but designers are already on top of this.\r\n- Eventually we want the Status app to allow users to mark messages, notifications and all sorts of things as unread as well. So giving the user full control of what's read/unread.\r\n- There's a new proposal to improve how the badge counter of the AC is displayed. Currently it only displays a blue icon or nothing, but this will change to: 1) When new notifications arrive -> blue icon on the bell. 2) When we open AC -> blue icon goes gray, 3) When we have all notifications marked as read - > hide icon.",
